WEBVTT

00:06.464 --> 00:12.846
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

00:36.995 --> 00:38.997
You left the tag on.

00:38.997 --> 00:42.041
Everything I do has a purpose, <i>muchacho.</i>

00:44.294 --> 00:46.171
It's a good plan, boss.

00:46.171 --> 00:49.382
Classic blitzkrieg.
Worked in Poland.

00:51.676 --> 00:52.635
Shall we?

00:54.220 --> 00:56.681
ROLANDO "MUSCULITO" MARTINEZ:
Okay. Okay. Fan out.

00:58.099 --> 00:59.392
Slow. Slow.

01:01.186 --> 01:02.187
Let's go.

01:08.943 --> 01:11.070
<i>En serio, alúmbrame,
aquí, ¿okay?</i>

01:11.070 --> 01:13.490
- BERNARD "MACHO" BARKER:
- Okay.

01:25.710 --> 01:28.213
<i>Chico, un momento,
no me apure.</i>

01:28.213 --> 01:29.339
What?

01:29.339 --> 01:31.299
Don't worry, boss.
He's gonna get it.

01:31.299 --> 01:33.843
Oh, good.
- Okay.

01:37.597 --> 01:39.182
<i>Pasa de grado.</i>

01:40.433 --> 01:41.601
<i>Villo, ¿qué pasa?</i>

01:42.727 --> 01:43.978
These are the wrong tools.

01:43.978 --> 01:46.564
What? He has
the wrong tools.

01:46.564 --> 01:48.483
How is that even possible?

01:48.483 --> 01:51.069
- I have right tools!
- He has the right tools.

01:51.569 --> 01:52.654
In Miami.

01:55.490 --> 01:58.243
I'm so sorry, boss.

01:58.243 --> 02:01.287
Let's go. <i>Vamanos.</i>

02:04.499 --> 02:09.254
♪ (THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:18.304 --> 02:19.848
♪ (THEME MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

02:23.268 --> 02:26.729
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:37.615 --> 02:40.410
<i>- Entrez-vous.</i>

02:43.663 --> 02:46.958
Howard, I just read the copy
for the HEW account.

02:46.958 --> 02:49.627
It's not quite there yet.

02:49.627 --> 02:51.671
The section
on the Child Safety Act.

02:51.671 --> 02:54.048
It just seems flavorless.

02:55.133 --> 02:57.218
So, you want me to make

02:58.011 --> 03:01.222
choking kids more spicy?

03:01.222 --> 03:03.099
Well--
- Christ, Spence,

03:03.099 --> 03:06.269
is that my legacy?
Working on this garbage.

03:06.269 --> 03:09.230
We really need you
to be a little more grateful

03:09.230 --> 03:10.607
for this job, Howard.

03:10.607 --> 03:13.776
Remember, you were unhireable
when the agency dumped you.

03:21.868 --> 03:24.245
<i>This week marks
the tenth anniversary</i>

03:24.245 --> 03:25.538
<i>of the failed invasion</i>

03:25.538 --> 03:28.833
<i>by Cuban exiles to overthrow
Castro, more commonly known</i>

03:28.833 --> 03:30.376
<i>as the Bay of Pigs.</i>
Howard?

03:30.376 --> 03:32.170
Howard, phone!
<i>The botched invasion</i>

03:32.170 --> 03:34.464
<i>pushed Cuba closer
to the Soviet Union.</i>

03:34.464 --> 03:35.715
<i>Repercussions of this event</i>

03:35.715 --> 03:38.968
<i>continue to this day,
where it is now widely seen</i>

03:38.968 --> 03:41.137
<i>as the largest CIA failure ever.</i>

03:41.137 --> 03:43.932
CIA my ass!
It was that chicken-shit

03:43.932 --> 03:46.935
Kennedy's fault.

03:52.482 --> 03:53.483
Sunny boy...

03:53.483 --> 03:55.485
...you know,
you're a half-step flat.

03:55.485 --> 03:58.321
It's like an ice pick
to the temple.

03:58.321 --> 04:01.449
Sorry, Papa. I-- I thought
you were s-- upstairs.

04:01.449 --> 04:03.660
What is that? Daniel Ellsberg.

04:03.660 --> 04:07.038
How did this leftist propaganda
end up in my house?

04:07.914 --> 04:09.165
We subscribe.

04:10.041 --> 04:11.084
Howard?

04:12.001 --> 04:14.003
Howard! Are you deaf?

04:15.338 --> 04:18.341
It's the White House.
Charles Colson.

04:19.676 --> 04:22.512
- You hear that?
- ♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

04:23.763 --> 04:26.140
They can't blame me forever.
I told you they'd call.

04:26.140 --> 04:28.101
Please just listen
to what they have to say.

04:28.101 --> 04:29.310
Huh.
Try not to be such

04:29.310 --> 04:31.604
- an asshole.
- Papa! Can you and me go--

04:31.604 --> 04:33.481
Papa's gotta an important call
now, kiddo.

04:33.481 --> 04:36.442
Maybe we can celebrate
after with some ice cream.

04:36.442 --> 04:38.486
And it's "Might you and I."

04:38.486 --> 04:40.613
Ice cream!
- Howard Hunt.

04:40.613 --> 04:42.699
<i>Please hold for Mr. Colson.</i>

04:42.699 --> 04:44.075
Yes, I'll hold.

04:52.750 --> 04:54.544
"He grabbed
the secret plans

04:54.544 --> 04:57.714
from her roughly.
'Oh, Jake. Oh, you bastard.'"

04:57.714 --> 04:59.590
Hey!

05:02.176 --> 05:04.679
Does anybody actually read
Papa's books?

05:04.679 --> 05:07.473
- I'm just the typist.
- Chuck! How the hell are you?

05:07.473 --> 05:09.183
<i>Howard,
the President asked</i>

05:09.183 --> 05:10.476
<i>for a real son of a bitch</i>

05:10.476 --> 05:12.395
<i>to handle this Pentagon
papers leak.</i>

05:12.395 --> 05:13.646
<i>I naturally thought of you.</i>

05:13.646 --> 05:15.440
- What do you need?
- ♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:15.440 --> 05:17.608
<i>A Boston judge
is now deciding</i>

05:17.608 --> 05:18.818
<i>if Daniel Ellsberg,</i>

05:18.818 --> 05:21.362
<i>who leaked the Pentagon papers,
may be extradited...</i>

05:21.362 --> 05:23.531
Move!

05:23.531 --> 05:25.158
<i>From the President on down,</i>

05:25.158 --> 05:27.201
<i>the administration is determined
to discourage</i>

05:27.201 --> 05:30.830
<i>any future leaks.
NBC News, Washington.</i>

05:34.375 --> 05:36.210
EGIL "BUD" KROGH: <i>Colson speaks
very highly of you.</i>

05:36.210 --> 05:37.170
<i>That's good to hear.</i>

05:37.170 --> 05:39.422
He doesn't speak highly
of anyone.

05:39.422 --> 05:41.340
Nor do they of him.

05:41.340 --> 05:44.469
Jesting. Please don't tell him
I said that.

05:44.469 --> 05:45.762
Of course not.

05:45.762 --> 05:47.513
SIU has been a long time coming,

05:47.513 --> 05:49.015
but this Pentagon
papers business

05:49.015 --> 05:50.141
was the final straw.

05:50.141 --> 05:52.769
The country's going to hell
in a hand-basket.

05:52.769 --> 05:54.437
Goddamn Jane Fonda.

05:54.437 --> 05:56.564
People need to understand
they cannot violate

05:56.564 --> 05:59.025
our national security
and get away with it.

05:59.025 --> 06:00.443
The President feels
there's been too much

06:00.443 --> 06:01.736
heel-dragging
on these leaks.

06:01.736 --> 06:03.988
Heel-dragging and pussyfooting.

06:05.823 --> 06:07.784
If there's one thing
I detest more

06:07.784 --> 06:10.161
than heel-dragging,
it's pussyfooting.

06:10.161 --> 06:12.497
Son of a bitch
steals 7,000 pages

06:12.497 --> 06:14.457
of top-secret documents
and gives it

06:14.457 --> 06:17.418
to the goddamn press?
High treason!

06:17.418 --> 06:19.879
I told Colson I think Ellsberg
should be...

06:20.838 --> 06:22.548
tarred and feathered and hanged.

06:22.548 --> 06:23.883
Well, then,
you and the President

06:23.883 --> 06:25.093
are of the same mind.

06:25.093 --> 06:27.845
Hence, SIU.
Special Intelligence Unit.

06:27.845 --> 06:28.888
Oh, look, right.

06:28.888 --> 06:31.099
Uh, Bud, I-- I--
I don't mean to step on

06:31.099 --> 06:32.934
any toes here
but, uh,

06:32.934 --> 06:35.061
"Special Intelligence"
makes it sound

06:35.061 --> 06:37.939
like we're, uh,
mentally handicapped.

06:39.357 --> 06:40.274
That had not occurred to me.

06:40.274 --> 06:41.609
Just make sure he does it

06:41.609 --> 06:43.152
- quickly this time.
- John.

06:43.694 --> 06:45.196
- Bud.
- Oh!

06:46.280 --> 06:49.742
Well, this must be the,
uh, the master spy.

06:49.742 --> 06:51.494
Howard Hunt, John Dean,

06:51.494 --> 06:52.703
White House Counsel.

06:53.412 --> 06:54.330
John.

06:55.164 --> 06:56.624
What a pleasure to meet you.

06:57.125 --> 06:58.918
Likewise, Hunt.

06:58.918 --> 07:01.337
Good luck
with your little project.

07:06.008 --> 07:07.135
Don't mind Dean.

07:07.135 --> 07:08.678
He thought SIU
should have been his,

07:08.678 --> 07:10.179
but between us,

07:10.179 --> 07:13.224
the President thinks he
has too much old lady in him.

07:13.224 --> 07:16.102
Yeah, well,
that explains the hairdo.

07:18.146 --> 07:20.022
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
I want you to meet

07:20.022 --> 07:22.316
Gordon Liddy.
We worked narcotics together

07:22.316 --> 07:24.652
at Treasury. You'll like him.

07:24.652 --> 07:27.363
Toughest guy I know.
He has a thing that he does

07:27.363 --> 07:29.949
to prove his commitment.
He'll hold his hand

07:29.949 --> 07:31.784
in the flame of a candle.

07:32.785 --> 07:35.538
And? What's the trick?

07:35.538 --> 07:37.248
There isn't one.
Gets third-degree burns

07:37.248 --> 07:40.668
every time, never flinches.
He's a great guy.

07:40.668 --> 07:42.295
Real family man.
Don't touch me!

07:42.295 --> 07:44.130
Gordon.

07:44.130 --> 07:47.717
Now, you're going to thrust
that right there.

07:47.717 --> 07:50.094
Right through
the pervert's cartilage,

07:50.094 --> 07:55.474
straight up and into the brain.
And voilà, threat neutralized.

07:55.474 --> 07:57.518
Gordon Liddy.
This is Howard Hunt.

07:57.518 --> 07:58.436
Huh.

07:58.436 --> 08:00.563
Colson made you sound
like a, uh...

08:01.856 --> 08:06.736
- regular James Bond.
- Funny, he never mentioned you.

08:06.736 --> 08:11.365
Uh, for the record,
James Bond is a work of fiction.

08:11.365 --> 08:14.202
I am the real deal.

08:14.202 --> 08:15.870
Oh.
- I write fiction,

08:15.870 --> 08:18.164
so I know the difference.

08:18.164 --> 08:20.374
Howard and Colson are both
Brown men.

08:20.374 --> 08:22.793
Oh! Where'd you go
to school, amigo?

08:22.793 --> 08:23.961
Ah, Fordham.

08:23.961 --> 08:26.255
Hmm, they teach you
that pencil business at Fordham?

08:26.255 --> 08:28.424
We're told Ellsberg
is seeing a psychiatrist.

08:28.424 --> 08:33.012
Uh, Bud, uh, I had a few ideas
about Ellsberg.

08:33.012 --> 08:34.764
You know, I think he might be--

08:34.764 --> 08:36.807
There's been
a spate of rapes

08:37.308 --> 08:38.559
in the area.

08:38.559 --> 08:40.686
So, I've been teaching
the girls in the office

08:40.686 --> 08:43.856
a little basic self-defense.

08:43.856 --> 08:48.069
Well, let us pray those rapes
happen near pencil sharpeners.

08:48.069 --> 08:49.695
- Gentlemen.
- See, Hunt,

08:49.695 --> 08:51.864
here at SIU, I try
and teach my people

08:51.864 --> 08:53.991
to embrace the unorthodox.

08:53.991 --> 08:56.786
Dream the impossible.
Your people?

08:57.995 --> 08:59.247
Bud, uh...

08:59.247 --> 09:01.457
...maybe
I'm a little confused here,

09:01.457 --> 09:04.043
Colson told me
that SIU was my op.

09:04.043 --> 09:06.087
With you providing oversight,
of course.

09:06.087 --> 09:09.924
You have been given
erroneous information.

09:10.883 --> 09:12.301
SIU is mine.

09:12.301 --> 09:15.429
Everybody knows SIU
is a Gordon Liddy operation.

09:15.429 --> 09:17.265
Gentlemen.
As per the President,

09:17.265 --> 09:19.308
I will be heading up SIU.

09:19.308 --> 09:21.978
You two will work together,
you will report to me.

09:21.978 --> 09:24.146
That's the arrangement.
Take it or leave it.

09:26.899 --> 09:28.609
- Roger that, amigo.
- Copacetic.

09:30.861 --> 09:37.493
♪ (NOSTALGIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

09:50.131 --> 09:54.218
Nothing makes my heart pound
like a well-tailored pair

09:54.218 --> 09:55.344
of riding pants.

09:55.344 --> 09:59.932
You are such
a simple man, Mr. Hunt.

10:01.392 --> 10:03.019
Sounds like someone's
had a good day.

10:03.019 --> 10:04.103
I did indeed.

10:04.854 --> 10:06.022
Makes one of us.

10:07.231 --> 10:08.399
What's the matter?

10:09.275 --> 10:10.735
Lisa's been calling.

10:12.069 --> 10:13.279
In tears.

10:13.279 --> 10:15.948
It's goddamn
American University,

10:15.948 --> 10:17.158
it's not Harvard.

10:17.158 --> 10:20.077
Apparently, her professors
do not understand her.

10:20.077 --> 10:21.370
Join the club.

10:30.046 --> 10:34.383
- Mm, really good curry, Mama.
- Oh, thank you, sweetie.

10:34.383 --> 10:38.262
Mm. Next time,
perhaps fewer raisins.

10:38.262 --> 10:39.388
No, thank you.

10:39.388 --> 10:42.058
I've got some good news!
They're setting me up

10:42.058 --> 10:46.062
in the White House.
Office with the secretary.

10:46.062 --> 10:48.647
The West Wing?
- Well, the EOB.

10:48.647 --> 10:51.025
Which is still considered
the White House.

10:51.025 --> 10:52.360
Cool!
Only to people

10:52.360 --> 10:54.195
who work in the EOB.

10:56.405 --> 10:58.324
Are you going to meet
the President?

10:58.324 --> 11:01.410
Well,
- it's funny you ask that.
It's...

11:02.495 --> 11:04.163
probably Lisa again.

11:04.705 --> 11:05.623
Hi, Honey.

11:05.623 --> 11:08.626
Actually, Papa already met
the President

11:08.626 --> 11:09.752
when he was vice president.

11:09.752 --> 11:12.755
We had dinner together
in Mexico.

11:12.755 --> 11:15.716
Wow!
The spicy food, sadly,

11:15.716 --> 11:17.259
did not agree with him,

11:17.259 --> 11:20.054
so he ordered cottage cheese.
With ketchup.

11:20.054 --> 11:21.347
...if you're crying.

11:21.347 --> 11:26.268
Oh, Christ! Is it too much
to ask to enjoy one damn meal?

11:26.268 --> 11:29.188
I'll call you back after dinner.
I-- I love you.

11:33.609 --> 11:35.277
Is Lisa going back
to the nuthouse?

11:35.277 --> 11:38.406
No, sweetie.
Don't call it that.

11:38.406 --> 11:40.449
It was a hospital.

11:40.449 --> 11:43.911
Christ. All that money
to all those doctors,

11:43.911 --> 11:46.080
right down the commode!

11:46.080 --> 11:48.916
Oh, come on, David.
Let's go wa-- wa--

11:48.916 --> 11:50.876
watch some TV.

11:52.211 --> 11:54.505
It's been five years
since the car accident.

11:54.505 --> 11:58.050
I mean, she should be better
by now.

11:58.050 --> 12:01.679
It wasn't just the accident,
Howard. You know that.

12:02.555 --> 12:04.348
Leave my plate in the icebox.

12:06.517 --> 12:08.978
Howard, we need to have
a serious talk.

12:08.978 --> 12:13.232
Not today. Today is a good day.

12:19.071 --> 12:20.614
<i>One, two,
three, four!</i>

12:20.614 --> 12:22.575
<i>We don't want your fucking war!</i>

12:22.575 --> 12:24.452
- ♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- One, two, three, four!

12:24.452 --> 12:25.786
We don't want your fucking war!

12:25.786 --> 12:43.179
One, two, three, four!
We don't want your fucking war!

12:43.179 --> 12:45.973
One, two, three, four!
We don't want your fucking...

12:45.973 --> 12:48.267
These are the latest
wiretap transcripts.

12:48.267 --> 12:50.102
We have taps
on Ellsberg's phones,

12:50.102 --> 12:52.897
as well as those
of his family, associates,

12:52.897 --> 12:54.982
even his Beverly Hills psychiatrist.

12:56.358 --> 12:59.487
I'll be candid, gentlemen.
We don't have a hell of a lot.

12:59.487 --> 13:02.156
I'm sure Ellsberg knows
that his phone is tapped.

13:02.156 --> 13:04.950
- He's no fool.
- What does it say in the file?

13:04.950 --> 13:06.702
Uh, from the psychiatrist?

13:06.702 --> 13:09.079
Dr. Fielding refused to turn it
over to us.

13:09.079 --> 13:11.499
Doctor-patient privilege.

13:11.499 --> 13:14.835
Clearly,
they're hiding something.

13:14.835 --> 13:17.338
And what they're hiding
is that Ellsberg

13:17.338 --> 13:20.216
is a communist agent.

13:20.216 --> 13:24.011
Connect the dots. Who benefits
from the world thinking

13:24.011 --> 13:29.475
that we can't win in Vietnam?
Hanoi, Russia, China, Cuba.

13:29.475 --> 13:31.810
We have no hard evidence
he's a spy.

13:31.810 --> 13:34.230
- Yet.
- A line has been crossed.

13:34.230 --> 13:37.816
Ellsberg needs to be taken down,
publicly discredited and fast.

13:37.816 --> 13:41.445
The President wants extensive
polygraph tests from everyone

13:41.445 --> 13:46.992
with high-level access.
DOD, CIA, FBI and State.

13:46.992 --> 13:48.577
I've taken the liberty
of compiling a list

13:48.577 --> 13:52.206
of 500 or so names,
grouped by department.

13:52.957 --> 13:54.917
Five hundred?

13:54.917 --> 13:57.753
Things have changed quite a bit
since your brief stint

13:57.753 --> 13:59.296
with the Bureau, Gordon.

13:59.296 --> 14:00.673
Director Hoover
doesn't believe

14:00.673 --> 14:02.091
in lie detectors anymore.

14:02.091 --> 14:05.177
Our machines are in a basement,
gathering dust.

14:05.177 --> 14:08.764
Well, if we're going to turn
the rats on each other,

14:08.764 --> 14:13.227
we need to create a climate
of fear and distrust.

14:13.227 --> 14:15.437
<i>Nacht und nebel.</i>

14:17.231 --> 14:18.857
Night and fog.

14:18.857 --> 14:21.819
We are not the White House's
gestapo.

14:27.199 --> 14:29.201
The President wants these polygraphs.

14:29.201 --> 14:30.244
This is a direct order.

14:30.244 --> 14:32.288
If the President
has any questions,

14:32.288 --> 14:34.707
he's welcome to call
Director Hoover.

14:34.707 --> 14:36.917
I assure you,
the FBI is committed

14:36.917 --> 14:40.045
with all legal means
at our disposal to assist

14:40.045 --> 14:42.339
the White House
in stopping leaks.

14:43.882 --> 14:45.009
Gentlemen.

14:46.468 --> 14:48.721
Bud?

14:50.139 --> 14:51.348
Meeting adjourned.

14:59.398 --> 15:02.276
So, I guess it's just you
and me

15:02.276 --> 15:05.821
against the entire radical left?

15:05.821 --> 15:08.449
Sisyphus had it easy.

15:08.449 --> 15:11.744
If you and I are the guys
that nail Ellsberg,

15:11.744 --> 15:15.122
Nixon will love us.
And by extension,

15:15.122 --> 15:16.540
Project ODESSA!

15:17.708 --> 15:19.209
ODESSA?

15:19.209 --> 15:23.505
Oh, yeah. New name for SIU.
ODESSA is the secret network

15:23.505 --> 15:26.050
that helped the SS officers
get to South America.

15:26.050 --> 15:27.926
And how exactly does
that relate

15:27.926 --> 15:31.055
to our current national
security problems?

15:31.055 --> 15:33.140
I already had
the stationery made.

15:33.140 --> 15:36.060
You made stationery
for a covert op?

15:36.060 --> 15:38.729
We got to get that file

15:38.729 --> 15:40.648
from the psychiatrist.

15:40.648 --> 15:43.984
- Fielding.
- What kind
of an idiot Soviet agent

15:43.984 --> 15:47.029
spills his guts to a shrink?

15:47.029 --> 15:50.324
If the FBI can't get their hands
on the file, how would we?

15:51.241 --> 15:54.787
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

15:54.787 --> 15:56.455
We don't need to steal

15:56.455 --> 15:59.166
Ellsberg's actual
psychiatric file,

15:59.166 --> 16:01.877
just photograph it.
That will prove

16:01.877 --> 16:04.797
Hmm.
- ...he's in bed
with the Russians,

16:04.797 --> 16:06.965
and then we'll have
those Pentagon papers

16:06.965 --> 16:08.634
by the short-hairs.

16:08.634 --> 16:11.053
It's a simple black bag job, Bud.

16:11.053 --> 16:12.179
- A black bag job?
- Yeah.

16:12.179 --> 16:14.890
At the Company,
we call them black ops,

16:14.890 --> 16:16.141
it's a better name.

16:16.141 --> 16:18.936
The proverbial black bag refers
to the satchel

16:18.936 --> 16:21.730
in which one carries
one's tools.

16:21.730 --> 16:24.650
"Black Ops" is subtler.

16:24.650 --> 16:26.485
The point is, Bud,
Fielding will never know

16:26.485 --> 16:30.155
we were there. At this stage,
we're just talking recon,

16:30.155 --> 16:31.865
not infiltration.

16:31.865 --> 16:35.077
Yeah. Yeah, we'll scope out
the good doctor's building,

16:35.077 --> 16:37.621
hallways and see
if we can gain entry.

16:37.621 --> 16:39.164
A trip to Beverly Hills.

16:39.164 --> 16:41.792
The CIA will provide us
with cameras,

16:41.792 --> 16:44.128
documents, disguises.

16:44.128 --> 16:45.546
What kind of disguises?

16:46.338 --> 16:49.967
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:05.649 --> 17:07.151
Open.

17:07.151 --> 17:08.694
There you go.

17:08.694 --> 17:09.987
We need driver's licenses,

17:09.987 --> 17:11.739
pocket litter,
the whole kit and caboodle.

17:11.739 --> 17:13.240
Yeah. Try these.

17:13.240 --> 17:16.076
A standard issue 35-millimeter
camera as well

17:16.076 --> 17:20.289
as a low-light miniature.
And walkie-talkies.

17:20.289 --> 17:23.751
Walkies are all in use.
You'll have to supply your own.

17:23.751 --> 17:26.128
Here.

17:26.128 --> 17:27.963
Hey, how's that gait-alterer?

17:27.963 --> 17:30.632
Feels like I have a pebble
in my shoe.

17:30.632 --> 17:32.801
I got a pebble in my shoe.

17:32.801 --> 17:33.969
You sure this

17:33.969 --> 17:37.097
isn't too conspicuous
for a clandestine operation?

17:37.431 --> 17:38.640
Exactly!

17:38.640 --> 17:41.143
All they'll remember
about you is the gimmick.

17:41.143 --> 17:43.353
"How tall was he?"
"Not sure."

17:43.353 --> 17:44.646
"He walked with a limp."

17:44.646 --> 17:48.484
"Eye color?" "Can't remember."
"Uh, his hair was bizarre."

17:48.484 --> 17:50.652
"I couldn't tell
if it was a wig or not."

17:50.652 --> 17:53.113
Classic misdirection.

17:53.113 --> 17:54.490
Black ops 101.

17:54.490 --> 17:56.867
See!

17:56.867 --> 17:59.286
- He calls it "black bag."
- Oh!

18:01.038 --> 18:02.831
An FBI dipshit.

18:04.666 --> 18:10.464
♪ ("CRYSTAL BLUE PERSUASION"
BY TOMMY JAMES PLAYING) ♪

18:15.385 --> 18:20.808
<i>♪ Crystal blue persuasion
Mm-hmm ♪</i>

18:21.517 --> 18:24.228
<i>♪ It's a new vibration ♪</i>

18:24.228 --> 18:28.607
Oh!
How about this weather? Hmm.

18:29.566 --> 18:32.653
- Governor Ronald Reagan.
- Hmm.

18:32.653 --> 18:35.364
Oh, about two blocks.
You're going to take a right.

18:37.616 --> 18:39.910
Yup.
- Apparently, Warren Beatty
lives around here.

18:39.910 --> 18:42.746
- Paul Newman, too.
- Communists.

18:48.085 --> 18:50.337
You don't need
to exaggerate the limp.

18:50.337 --> 18:51.880
I'm not exaggerating.

18:52.798 --> 18:53.882
It hurts.

18:56.301 --> 18:57.594
That's Fielding's office.

19:02.641 --> 19:04.434
Get in the shot.
Like a tourist.

19:08.939 --> 19:10.148
Say "cheese!"

19:11.984 --> 19:14.027
Cheese!
Ah!

19:14.778 --> 19:15.904
Good.

19:20.701 --> 19:21.952
Ma'am!
Mm-hmm?

19:21.952 --> 19:24.663
Might you take a picture
of myself and my friend,

19:24.663 --> 19:26.874
George F. Leonard.
Of course.

19:26.874 --> 19:28.584
Thank you.
- Yeah.

19:28.584 --> 19:31.795
- Actually, no. Uh, here. Here.
- Oh.

19:33.964 --> 19:36.049
Smile, you're on vacation.

19:36.884 --> 19:38.302
Where are you two from?

19:38.302 --> 19:39.636
- Montana.
- Florida.

19:41.013 --> 19:45.726
Uh, okay. Smile!

19:45.726 --> 19:47.311
Yeah, next to the car.

19:49.062 --> 19:50.230
We're in a fucking alley.

19:50.230 --> 19:53.066
Yeah, you're in California.
Look like you're having fun.

19:53.066 --> 19:59.031
♪ (MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

19:59.031 --> 20:00.908
A little awkward.

20:07.831 --> 20:09.374
It is what it is.

20:11.835 --> 20:13.629
Hey! That was him!
I'm telling you.

20:13.629 --> 20:15.130
John Wayne
is not picking up

20:15.130 --> 20:17.424
his own dry cleaning.
That was the Duke!

20:20.218 --> 20:23.513
She saw us. Shit.
That's going to be a problem.

20:23.513 --> 20:25.891
Hold on. Uh, i-- if Consuela

20:25.891 --> 20:28.143
let's us in, there is no crime, right?

20:28.143 --> 20:30.896
- You are the lawyer.
- Ooh. Wait.

20:30.896 --> 20:33.398
- Let me think about--
<i>- Hola, señora.</i>

20:34.191 --> 20:37.277
Oh, <i>señorita.</i>

20:37.277 --> 20:41.281
<i>Somos, eh, doctores... y amigos</i>

20:41.281 --> 20:43.158
<i>de</i> Dr. Fielding.

20:54.795 --> 20:55.837
Okay.

20:57.798 --> 21:00.759
- What are we doing?
- You are going to leave

21:00.759 --> 21:02.427
a very important message

21:02.427 --> 21:05.222
for our dear friend,
Doctor Fielding.

21:05.222 --> 21:06.974
I will wait out here.

21:09.351 --> 21:10.644
<i>Sí!</i>

21:21.363 --> 21:22.614
<i>Gracias.</i>

21:25.867 --> 21:29.705
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

21:44.886 --> 21:46.346
<i>¿Ustedes son doctores?</i>

21:46.930 --> 21:49.099
<i>Sí, psiquiatras.</i>

21:51.476 --> 21:55.897
<i>Somos muy importante.</i>

21:57.357 --> 22:01.903
All done. With the note.

22:01.903 --> 22:05.157
Doctor, did you forget
your glasses?

22:07.367 --> 22:09.953
Yes. Farsighted.

22:09.953 --> 22:12.456
I can't see a thing
without them.

22:12.456 --> 22:13.790
<i>Gracias.</i>

22:17.210 --> 22:18.295
Did you photograph the file?

22:18.295 --> 22:19.504
No,
the cabinet was locked,

22:19.504 --> 22:21.631
But I shot the whole office.

22:21.631 --> 22:23.008
Mission accomplished,
come on!

22:23.008 --> 22:25.385
<i>♪ Out of the tree of life ♪</i>

22:25.385 --> 22:27.262
<i>♪ I just picked me a plum ♪</i>

22:30.432 --> 22:34.895
<i>♪ You came along
And everything started to hum ♪</i>

22:37.147 --> 22:41.568
<i>♪ Still it's a real good bet
The best is yet to come ♪</i>

22:44.529 --> 22:49.367
<i>♪ The best is yet to come
Come the day you're mine ♪</i>

22:53.330 --> 22:54.664
So good!

22:54.664 --> 22:57.918
Encore!

22:57.918 --> 23:00.837
Thank you! The band is going
to "take five."

23:00.837 --> 23:03.673
Please, be sure to tip
your waitress.

23:05.300 --> 23:07.636
That was wonderful,
Mr. Hamilton.

23:07.636 --> 23:10.055
Are you a professional musician?

23:10.055 --> 23:14.309
Uh, perhaps in a past life.

23:16.228 --> 23:18.855
Actually, on the QT,
my colleague and I

23:18.855 --> 23:22.692
just finished a top-secret
mission for President Nixon.

23:22.692 --> 23:24.653
Oh, Edward!
You bull-shitter, you.

23:24.653 --> 23:27.364
This guy.

23:27.364 --> 23:29.699
That's not true.

23:29.699 --> 23:31.701
By the way,
why don't you give me

23:31.701 --> 23:33.370
your number and address.

23:33.370 --> 23:35.247
I'll send you
my most recent book.

23:35.247 --> 23:38.333
I am a novelist as well.

23:38.333 --> 23:39.793
Really?
Yes.

23:39.793 --> 23:42.921
And, uh,
maybe when I'm in town--

23:42.921 --> 23:48.468
I have a top-secret mission
for you. One more beer, please.

23:48.468 --> 23:49.928
Uh, anything German.

23:52.305 --> 23:53.640
Oh, and some matches, please.

23:53.640 --> 23:56.017
Mm-hmm.
Yes.

23:57.269 --> 23:59.354
Hey, hey! What are you doing?

23:59.354 --> 24:02.858
Telling an airborne waitress
that we work for the President?

24:02.858 --> 24:07.988
Just blowing off steam, amigo.
Making new friends.

24:07.988 --> 24:10.740
I promise you,
she didn't believe a word of it.

24:16.580 --> 24:17.747
You okay?

24:19.040 --> 24:21.042
Goddamn ulcer.

24:23.003 --> 24:24.713
This helps.

24:24.713 --> 24:29.509
Look. Now, I appreciate
that you take chances

24:29.509 --> 24:32.179
and, yes, we've gotten results.

24:32.179 --> 24:35.473
But I can't have any fuckups, capisce?

24:35.473 --> 24:36.766
It's too important.

24:38.143 --> 24:42.731
Now, you listen to me, George.

24:42.731 --> 24:45.817
You are not
a federal agent anymore,

24:45.817 --> 24:49.613
you are an intelligence agent.

24:50.614 --> 24:52.532
You are a spy.

24:52.532 --> 24:55.660
And if you want to succeed
in this line of work,

24:55.660 --> 24:59.873
you need to be willing to bend
the rules,

25:00.624 --> 25:02.626
color outside the lines.

25:05.170 --> 25:06.838
Sorry, all we have is Budweiser.

25:06.838 --> 25:09.090
Oh, hell, yeah.
It sounds German, right?

25:11.509 --> 25:13.303
Oh, thank you.

25:16.848 --> 25:18.099
- What is that?
- Nothing.

25:18.099 --> 25:19.893
- Give me that.
- Don't even think twice.

25:19.893 --> 25:21.436
Give that!

25:21.436 --> 25:23.855
- You better let me see that!
- No, get away from--

25:23.855 --> 25:26.024
Let me see! Give it!

25:28.151 --> 25:29.194
Oh!

25:30.070 --> 25:33.114
Linda.

25:33.114 --> 25:36.201
You are a married man,
Mr. Hunt.

25:36.201 --> 25:40.247
Howard is. Edward is not.

25:40.247 --> 25:41.998
- ♪ (MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- Just like that!

25:41.998 --> 25:44.334
Just like that, Howard.

25:44.334 --> 25:47.462
- Ed-- Edward.
- What?

25:47.462 --> 25:49.005
Call me Edward.

25:49.005 --> 25:55.178
Right, yes, sorry. I...
Edward, just like that, Edward.

25:56.429 --> 25:58.014
Edward!

26:08.525 --> 26:11.319
The L.A. mission was a success.

26:13.863 --> 26:16.658
That explains it.

26:17.534 --> 26:20.120
It's all coming together, Dot.

26:20.120 --> 26:21.621
You know,
the kids have never been

26:21.621 --> 26:23.957
- to Paris.
<i>- Attends, chérie.</i>

26:25.166 --> 26:28.169
They're only paying me
a hundred dollars a day.

26:28.169 --> 26:29.587
Really?

26:29.587 --> 26:32.257
I thought the SIU
was your big comeback.

26:32.924 --> 26:34.050
Oh, it is.

26:34.843 --> 26:36.594
They just don't know it yet.

26:42.017 --> 26:45.395
Daniel Ellsberg's file
has to be in that cabinet.

26:45.395 --> 26:46.771
I have to say, fellas...

26:47.564 --> 26:48.690
I'm impressed.

26:48.690 --> 26:51.484
You should have seen this guy operate.

26:51.484 --> 26:53.236
He gets the cleaning lady

26:53.236 --> 26:56.281
to let us in.
Ergo, all 100 percent legal.

26:56.281 --> 26:57.490
And they can't ID us.

26:57.490 --> 26:59.326
Oh, yeah. Good luck with that.
And the best part.

26:59.326 --> 27:01.703
- When she leaves at night--
- Oh, yeah!

27:01.703 --> 27:03.246
She doesn't even lock
the back door.

27:03.246 --> 27:05.665
Slip in, get
into the filing cabinet,

27:05.665 --> 27:06.624
slip out.

27:06.624 --> 27:08.585
- In, out.
- Without anyone knowing.

27:09.294 --> 27:11.212
Textbook black op.

27:11.212 --> 27:13.381
Well, I'm going to run
your black bag op by Ehrlichman.

27:13.381 --> 27:16.551
But I think he is going
to like it.

27:18.178 --> 27:19.387
Great work.

27:19.387 --> 27:21.556
♪ (MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

27:28.271 --> 27:29.564
Plumbers?

27:29.564 --> 27:31.232
We fix leaks.

27:31.941 --> 27:32.692
Oh.

27:32.692 --> 27:35.111
I think everybody
prefers ODESSA.

27:36.196 --> 27:39.657
No, no. Plumbers is better.
Very clever.

27:41.701 --> 27:43.870
Thank you, Howard.

27:43.870 --> 27:45.205
Yeah.

27:45.205 --> 27:47.707
Come on, come on,
come on, we're running late.

27:47.707 --> 27:51.211
We're not late.
We're ten minutes early, Howard.

27:51.211 --> 27:54.255
- No, we're actually--
- Yes. We're ten minutes early.

27:54.255 --> 27:56.591
Uh, listen, he can be a lot
to take at first

27:56.591 --> 27:59.427
but, uh, he-- he kind of grows
on you.

27:59.427 --> 28:02.389
Hmm. Some people say
the same thing about you.

28:03.765 --> 28:06.142
- Psst! Just fix this.
- Please don't touch my hair.

28:06.142 --> 28:07.435
Howard.

28:07.435 --> 28:09.771
Welcome! I'm Frances.

28:09.771 --> 28:11.815
Come in, come in,
come in!

28:12.982 --> 28:16.236
Kids, I want you
to say hello to the Hunts.

28:16.236 --> 28:18.405
Hello!

28:18.405 --> 28:22.033
Uh, this is Jim, Tom, Grace,
Alexandra and Raymond.

28:22.033 --> 28:23.576
- Hello!
- Hello!

28:25.078 --> 28:26.329
Tom?

28:26.329 --> 28:28.623
Pleased to meet you,
Mr. and Mrs. Hunt.

28:28.623 --> 28:31.459
It's an honor to have
such distinguished members

28:31.459 --> 28:33.795
of the armed forces and,

28:33.795 --> 28:36.131
- uh...
- Foreign services.

28:36.131 --> 28:37.799
...foreign services in our home.

28:37.799 --> 28:40.343
And-- And may I say

28:40.343 --> 28:43.471
what an honor it is
to meet such polite

28:43.471 --> 28:47.976
and, uh, well-groomed
youngsters.

28:47.976 --> 28:49.519
Take their coats.

28:49.519 --> 28:51.146
May I please take your coat,
Mrs. Hunt?

28:51.146 --> 28:53.481
Oh, uh, yes, thank you.

28:53.481 --> 28:55.775
I hear you have a daughter
at Smith.

28:55.775 --> 28:57.652
Uh, yes, Kevan.

28:58.903 --> 29:02.949
What an unusual name
for a girl. Fun!

29:02.949 --> 29:05.869
Okay. Who would like a drink?

29:05.869 --> 29:07.454
Yes.

29:07.454 --> 29:08.872
There we go, upstairs.

29:11.374 --> 29:13.168
It's just been
"Howard this,"

29:13.168 --> 29:15.211
and "Howard that."
If Howard wasn't a man,

29:15.211 --> 29:16.963
- I'd be jealous!
- Well,

29:16.963 --> 29:18.715
- maybe you should be.
- Oh, stop!

29:18.715 --> 29:21.009
So, where did you two meet?

29:21.009 --> 29:23.178
Um, actually, we met in China.

29:23.178 --> 29:24.512
Oh!
- At work.

29:24.512 --> 29:25.805
So you're also a--

29:25.805 --> 29:28.683
Oh, I was. During the war,
I was involved in the recovery

29:28.683 --> 29:30.477
of art stolen by the Nazis.

29:30.477 --> 29:32.395
- Wow!
- Fascinating.

29:32.395 --> 29:33.855
Mm.
Just fascinating.

29:33.855 --> 29:36.065
Uh, I don't know,
I'm a history nut myself.

29:36.065 --> 29:37.233
- He is.
- Yeah.

29:37.233 --> 29:39.360
Well, actually,
I might have a little artifact

29:39.360 --> 29:41.738
- that you might find very...
- Oh!

29:41.738 --> 29:44.574
...interesting,
given your line of work.

29:44.574 --> 29:46.034
You know,
when I met Dot,

29:46.034 --> 29:47.368
she was formidable.

29:47.368 --> 29:49.829
Carried a gun,
spoke multiple languages,

29:49.829 --> 29:51.873
she was a veritable Bond girl.

29:51.873 --> 29:53.791
Now, I'm just
a suburban hausfrau.

29:55.251 --> 29:56.461
Nothing wrong with that.

29:56.461 --> 30:00.715
And she's also a "translator"
at the Spanish Embassy,

30:00.715 --> 30:03.009
- wink-wink.
- I heard that!

30:05.470 --> 30:08.014
- How did you two meet?
- His sister set us up.

30:08.014 --> 30:11.351
I selected Fran
for her high intelligence.

30:11.351 --> 30:13.102
She used to work at IBM.

30:13.102 --> 30:14.938
- Receptionist.
- And of course,

30:14.938 --> 30:16.523
her Celtic/Teutonic genes.

30:16.523 --> 30:19.108
Lineage is very important

30:19.108 --> 30:22.028
to Gordon. Even more so
than intelligence.

30:26.032 --> 30:28.952
I hope you all brought
your appetites tonight,

30:28.952 --> 30:32.247
because Franny
makes a mean roast.

30:32.247 --> 30:33.373
I love a good--

30:36.376 --> 30:38.836
- Is-- Is that Hitler?
- Yes.

30:44.008 --> 30:45.927
Franny, do you want to go check
the potatoes?

30:45.927 --> 30:49.681
I set a timer!
I'll hear it go off!

30:49.681 --> 30:51.432
See! Intelligence!

30:51.432 --> 30:54.143
Gordon, you don't happen
to have any jazz, do you?

30:54.143 --> 30:57.438
- No.
- Big band era? Benny Goodman?

30:57.438 --> 30:59.566
You know,
I know Gene Krupa--

30:59.566 --> 31:02.193
You met him once, Howard.
What is he yelling about?

31:02.193 --> 31:03.820
<i>Die Kunst Griechenlands.</i>

31:03.820 --> 31:06.155
What about showtunes?
You have any showtunes?

31:06.155 --> 31:09.033
No. This is better.
He's talking about art

31:09.033 --> 31:11.494
as propaganda
for the ancient Greeks.

31:11.494 --> 31:13.329
Of course, he's comparing
the Hellenic ideal

31:13.329 --> 31:14.664
to the Bolshevik--

31:14.664 --> 31:16.124
Oh, God!
- Oh!

31:16.124 --> 31:18.042
Franny, get down!

31:18.042 --> 31:20.253
Oh, it's okay!
Just eggs, Gordon.

31:20.253 --> 31:22.547
Just eggs. And some kids.

31:22.547 --> 31:26.426
Fran.
Those goddamn punks are back.

31:27.552 --> 31:29.470
I'm sorry everybody,
I'll be right back.

31:29.470 --> 31:31.139
Honey, we have guests.

31:32.724 --> 31:34.475
Why's he going upstairs?

31:34.475 --> 31:35.893
Why don't you ask Hitler?

31:35.893 --> 31:38.021
This whole new house,
new school--

31:38.021 --> 31:40.857
It's been a bit
of an adjustment.

31:40.857 --> 31:43.443
Gordon told the boys
not to take any guff

31:43.443 --> 31:44.944
from the locals,
so they've gotten

31:44.944 --> 31:46.487
in their share of dust-ups.

31:46.487 --> 31:48.656
That's what the eggs
are about.

31:48.656 --> 31:51.576
Hmm.
- Such a waste of food.

31:51.576 --> 31:53.244
Boys can be so cruel.

31:53.244 --> 31:54.537
- I know.
- What?

31:54.537 --> 31:55.622
It doesn't matter, Howard.

31:55.622 --> 31:56.581
Boys.
Huh?

31:56.581 --> 31:58.791
- Boys!
- Can I freshen your drink?

31:58.791 --> 32:00.043
Mm-hmm.

32:01.544 --> 32:03.671
Do you mind to turn
that down a little bit?

32:03.671 --> 32:04.922
What?

32:10.470 --> 32:11.679
Cheese?

32:11.679 --> 32:15.224
We have all three.
Cheddar, Swiss and Jarlsberg.

32:15.224 --> 32:18.478
Problem solved.

32:18.478 --> 32:20.229
Gordon, your leg again.

32:20.229 --> 32:21.898
We had a civilized chat

32:21.898 --> 32:24.817
and after a little old-fashioned
arm twisting,

32:24.817 --> 32:27.737
they agreed to take
their carousing elsewhere.

32:27.737 --> 32:30.907
Grace! Ice pack!
Coming, Mother!

32:32.075 --> 32:34.243
The potatoes!
Oh, delicious!

32:41.084 --> 32:42.794
So.

32:43.503 --> 32:44.796
I-- I know.

32:44.796 --> 32:47.632
- The Nazi stuff.
- Yes.

32:51.094 --> 32:53.680
- And the gun.
- I know.

32:55.139 --> 32:57.684
The sooner you are done
with this guy, the better.

33:02.814 --> 33:04.232
Fran seems nice.

33:15.910 --> 33:18.329
Gordon. I've got some
very good news.

33:18.329 --> 33:20.206
- Hello, Bud.
- Where's Hunt?

33:20.206 --> 33:21.791
Bud.

33:21.791 --> 33:24.043
Yes? Good!

33:24.043 --> 33:25.878
Ellsberg mission is a go.

33:25.878 --> 33:27.922
But you two cannot make
the entry yourselves.

33:27.922 --> 33:29.882
You are White House employees
on the payroll.

33:29.882 --> 33:32.009
Hmm.
- We'll get outside help.

33:32.009 --> 33:33.261
Exchange that
for fresh cash

33:33.261 --> 33:34.846
at a bank so it isn't traceable.

33:34.846 --> 33:37.765
Call me when it's done
and for God's sake,

33:37.765 --> 33:40.560
don't get caught.

33:41.853 --> 33:44.313
<i>♪ Look over yonder ♪</i>

33:46.315 --> 33:50.903
<i>♪ A new day is comin'
Woo-hoo ♪</i>

33:50.903 --> 33:55.074
<i>♪ Crystal blue persuasion ♪</i>

33:55.074 --> 33:56.367
How are we looking?

33:57.702 --> 33:59.078
What kind of budget
is 2600 bucks

33:59.078 --> 34:01.748
- for this kind of op?
- It's not about the money.

34:01.748 --> 34:05.001
My boys would do it for free.
They're patriots.

34:05.001 --> 34:06.127
Oh!

34:07.044 --> 34:08.713
Real Americans.

34:09.213 --> 34:10.423
Better.

34:10.423 --> 34:15.845
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

34:23.936 --> 34:27.315
Oh. Uh, good afternoon.
Are you gentlemen checking in?

34:27.315 --> 34:28.524
We're not staying here.

34:28.524 --> 34:29.734
Excellent.

34:29.734 --> 34:31.569
Then you're more than welcome
to park in our garage.

34:35.656 --> 34:36.699
Okay.

34:45.792 --> 34:47.126
If you see
the maid,

34:47.126 --> 34:49.378
tell her we're out of soap.

34:49.378 --> 34:51.839
The wife gets pretty jazzed
when I bring these home

34:51.839 --> 34:53.591
from traveling.

34:53.591 --> 34:57.220
You are one romantic
son of a bitch, Gordon Liddy.

34:57.220 --> 35:00.139
Well, I try.

35:01.265 --> 35:02.475
It's the boys.

35:09.023 --> 35:11.234
We got off on six
and went up the stairs

35:11.234 --> 35:12.735
to make sure
we weren't followed.

35:12.735 --> 35:16.489
- We're on the seventh floor.
- He has the "angina."

35:18.157 --> 35:19.575
Take your nitro, Macho.

35:19.575 --> 35:21.828
Come here.

35:24.205 --> 35:26.999
Fellas, uh,
this is George F. Leonard.

35:26.999 --> 35:28.167
He's ex-FBI.

35:28.167 --> 35:32.088
George, this is Felipe De Diego,
Rolando Martinez,

35:32.088 --> 35:35.007
known as "Musculito,"
and Bernard Barker.

35:35.007 --> 35:37.093
-"Macho."
- Macho.

35:37.093 --> 35:38.803
Macho.

35:38.803 --> 35:43.766
A little birdie told me
you are all Bay of Pigs?

35:46.602 --> 35:49.814
- Hmm?
- ♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

35:49.814 --> 35:50.898
No.

35:53.568 --> 35:55.820
It's okay. He knows.

35:56.279 --> 35:57.488
Then yes.

36:00.533 --> 36:03.452
George, if you want a can't-lose
investment...

36:03.452 --> 36:05.037
Miami real estate--

36:05.037 --> 36:07.123
- Oh, I don't--
- If you ever want
to talk property.

36:07.123 --> 36:08.499
Gentlemen!
- Call me.

36:08.916 --> 36:10.001
Gentlemen.

36:10.543 --> 36:11.711
To old friends!

36:11.711 --> 36:14.297
To new beginnings,

36:14.297 --> 36:17.800
Cuba libre
and President Richard Nixon!

36:17.800 --> 36:19.385
Viva Nixon!

36:20.011 --> 36:21.220
And fuck Kennedy!

36:25.641 --> 36:27.143
Fuck Kennedy!

36:29.520 --> 36:32.440
Fuck Kennedy!

36:35.318 --> 36:40.990
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

36:47.955 --> 36:49.081
Any sign?

36:49.081 --> 36:51.751
No.
Fielding is still in his office.

36:51.751 --> 36:54.962
- What is that?
- This?

36:54.962 --> 36:58.424
ZF-41 sniper scope.
World War II vintage.

36:59.216 --> 37:00.927
German, of course.

37:01.802 --> 37:04.055
Of course. Gordon...

37:04.889 --> 37:06.140
I have to ask.

37:07.224 --> 37:09.685
What's with the Hitler hard-on?

37:10.895 --> 37:13.481
You know, a lot of us fought
in the war.

37:16.025 --> 37:17.276
I'm no Nazi.

37:18.152 --> 37:19.654
Believe me.

37:19.654 --> 37:21.614
And I understand
what those people did

37:21.614 --> 37:26.077
was pure evil.
But before the war,

37:26.077 --> 37:29.413
Hoboken was a pretty rough town
and I...

37:31.540 --> 37:33.459
I was a scrawny little mick,

37:33.459 --> 37:36.337
and used to get
the shit kicked out of me daily.

37:36.337 --> 37:38.381
Scared to even leave the house.

37:39.423 --> 37:42.885
And my nanny, German,
Frau Teresa,

37:42.885 --> 37:45.471
she used to put
Hitler's speeches on,

37:45.471 --> 37:47.390
you know, on radio.

37:47.390 --> 37:50.226
And there was something
about that voice,

37:50.226 --> 37:56.440
just filled me with the will
to just get out there

37:56.440 --> 38:00.444
and conquer my fears.
And Der Hindenburg.

38:00.444 --> 38:03.072
She used to fly
right above my house.

38:03.072 --> 38:05.616
The most incredible sight
I'd ever seen.

38:06.450 --> 38:07.785
Bigger than a battleship!

38:09.870 --> 38:11.163
Have you ever considered

38:11.163 --> 38:15.001
that Adolf Hitler
and Der Hindenburg

38:15.001 --> 38:17.712
are not ideal templates
for success?

38:19.338 --> 38:21.882
You know, well,
inspiring nonetheless.

38:23.968 --> 38:27.013
Oh! There's Fielding.
We got him.

38:27.013 --> 38:29.098
I know. I can see him
with my naked eye.

38:29.098 --> 38:30.641
- He's right there.
- ♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

38:30.641 --> 38:32.810
He's heading to his car,
get ready to follow him.

38:32.810 --> 38:34.520
I'm going to call
the Cubans.

38:35.813 --> 38:37.732
Unit One to Unit Two,

38:37.732 --> 38:40.401
the eagle has left the nest. Over.

38:46.657 --> 38:47.658
Copy that, over.

38:47.658 --> 38:49.952
These things are garbage, <i>muchacho.</i>

38:49.952 --> 38:52.788
I spent every dime
that Bud gave us.

38:52.788 --> 38:54.498
Oh! That's him, hold this.

38:54.498 --> 38:56.917
Yeah.

38:56.917 --> 38:58.586
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

38:58.586 --> 39:00.504
- Not too close.
- I know.

39:02.548 --> 39:04.050
- Speed up!
- Right.

39:06.260 --> 39:07.762
Oh, Jesus.

39:07.762 --> 39:12.349
Shit! You okay?

39:12.349 --> 39:15.561
Pain is a mental construct.

39:33.746 --> 39:35.748
Shrink's got a nice house.

39:53.766 --> 39:56.519
What a job
this poor mope has.

39:56.519 --> 39:59.396
Listening to pantywaists
like Ellsberg,

39:59.396 --> 40:01.649
who whine about their mothers
all day.

40:03.067 --> 40:06.320
I'm so angry at my mom!

40:06.320 --> 40:10.074
I saw a psychiatrist.

40:12.451 --> 40:13.452
Oh.

40:14.078 --> 40:15.329
A couple of times.

40:16.705 --> 40:19.125
My kids were in a car accident,
years ago.

40:20.501 --> 40:22.920
My eldest, Lisa, she--

40:22.920 --> 40:25.214
she banged her head
up pretty badly.

40:25.214 --> 40:27.466
- Hmm.
- It...

40:30.344 --> 40:31.387
affected her.

40:33.931 --> 40:34.932
Well...

40:36.976 --> 40:41.772
A man has got to take care
of his family.

40:48.571 --> 40:53.325
All right. Uh, I'll stay here
and keep eyes on Fielding.

40:53.325 --> 40:55.786
You head back, run point
on the Cubans

40:55.786 --> 40:59.456
in the entry.
Any hang-ups, radio me.

40:59.456 --> 41:00.541
Roger that.

41:01.500 --> 41:02.543
Oh!

41:04.295 --> 41:05.254
Thanks.

41:28.485 --> 41:33.616
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

41:54.136 --> 41:55.763
Heading
to the back door now.

41:55.763 --> 42:01.227
We are a go. The patient
is with the doctor, over.

42:06.148 --> 42:09.818
Uh, do not copy.
Uh, uh, uh... Wait a minute.

42:13.822 --> 42:14.698
Repeat.

42:15.658 --> 42:18.994
Eagle is in the nest. Over.

42:18.994 --> 42:21.163
Do not copy. Repeat. Over.

42:21.163 --> 42:24.917
I said, "The eagle is still
in the nest."

42:28.003 --> 42:30.631
I can't understand
you either, please.

42:32.675 --> 42:36.136
I said the eagle
is in the goddamn nest!

42:36.136 --> 42:37.471
The nest!

42:37.471 --> 42:41.016
Press the button all the way in
and speak clearly. Don't shout.

42:46.772 --> 42:47.856
Fuck!

42:47.856 --> 42:50.359
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

42:50.359 --> 42:52.778
George? We've got a problem.

42:54.071 --> 42:55.406
What kind of problem?

42:56.865 --> 42:59.451
It's locked. We radioed you.

42:59.451 --> 43:01.412
These walkie-talkies
are shit, man.

43:01.412 --> 43:02.705
Hey!

43:02.705 --> 43:06.000
- Do not blame the equipment!
- Okay. Okay.

43:06.000 --> 43:08.961
Damn it.
It was supposed to be open.

43:10.170 --> 43:12.923
- Any other way in?
- Well...

43:12.923 --> 43:15.718
there's that.
But that one's locked, too.

43:15.718 --> 43:17.344
Break the goddamn window.

43:21.015 --> 43:23.058
<i>¿Qué te pasó?</i>
My wrist!

43:23.058 --> 43:25.811
Move, move, move.

43:34.028 --> 43:36.989
Shit, shit, shit!

43:36.989 --> 43:44.121
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

43:45.748 --> 43:48.083
- Fielding's out of pocket!
- What?

43:48.083 --> 43:50.878
- We have to get the boys out!
- Why didn't you radio me?

43:50.878 --> 43:53.380
Fellas? Can you hear me?
<i>That's why!</i>

43:53.380 --> 43:55.090
Ow.

43:55.090 --> 43:56.675
Oh! There they are!

43:59.053 --> 44:01.930
<i>Muchachos, vamos!
Vamos, vamos, vamos!</i>

44:01.930 --> 44:04.016
No, no, no!

44:23.577 --> 44:27.039
Okay, full debriefing.
Did we get the file?

44:27.039 --> 44:28.916
There was no Ellsberg file.

44:29.708 --> 44:31.085
Shit!

44:31.085 --> 44:32.753
- You're sure? Nothing?
- Nada.

44:32.753 --> 44:35.214
We went through every file
in that office, man.

44:35.214 --> 44:37.049
We took Polaroids. Nada.

44:38.926 --> 44:42.429
- Rosenberg, Goldberg, Grodberg.
<i>- Pero</i> Ellsberg, no.

44:42.429 --> 44:43.722
<i>Scheisse!</i>

44:43.722 --> 44:45.557
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:45.557 --> 44:48.268
So, we know the file was moved.

44:51.605 --> 44:52.648
<i>Bien hecho.</i>

44:52.648 --> 44:53.982
What are we celebrating?

44:53.982 --> 45:00.239
Well, dollars to donuts,
the file is in Fielding's house.

45:00.239 --> 45:05.160
So to our next mission,
<i>adelante!</i>

45:05.160 --> 45:07.079
<i>Adelante!</i>

45:07.079 --> 45:10.332
- Viva Nixon!
- Viva Nixon!

45:10.332 --> 45:12.251
Eduardo.
You need to see this.

45:12.251 --> 45:14.878
Edward!

45:33.981 --> 45:35.023
Macho...

45:36.859 --> 45:38.318
what happened?

45:38.318 --> 45:39.903
We had a little trouble
with the lock

45:39.903 --> 45:41.113
on the filing cabinet.

45:41.113 --> 45:42.739
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
<i>It broke.</i>

45:42.739 --> 45:44.199
<i>So we had to improvise.</i>

45:47.953 --> 45:50.789
Hey!

45:50.789 --> 45:52.332
You know,
the whole point

45:52.332 --> 45:55.210
of the operation, Macho,
was for Fielding

45:55.210 --> 45:57.379
to never know
that we were there.

45:57.379 --> 45:59.631
George told us
to break the window!

45:59.631 --> 46:01.425
- I didn't--
- Jesus, Gordon!

46:01.425 --> 46:02.593
Who's Gordon?

46:04.553 --> 46:06.972
You tore the place apart.

46:06.972 --> 46:08.891
Why is all this shit
on the floor!

46:08.891 --> 46:11.768
Oh, <i>tranquilo! Tranquilo!</i>
We come up with a plan.

46:11.768 --> 46:14.897
We made a mess,
threw some pills around

46:14.897 --> 46:18.650
<i>to make it seem like junkies
were looking for drugs.</i>

46:19.985 --> 46:21.445
Where did you get the pills?

46:21.445 --> 46:24.740
We broke into a doctor's office
down the hall.

46:24.740 --> 46:27.701
May I ask a question?

46:28.327 --> 46:29.286
<i>Ay, caramba.</i>

46:29.286 --> 46:31.497
What kind
of a drug addict,

46:31.497 --> 46:36.084
A, brings his own drugs
to a crime scene.

46:36.960 --> 46:41.381
And B, scatters them
about the floor

46:41.381 --> 46:43.800
and leaves them behind!

46:45.469 --> 46:47.262
That's a fair point.
That's a fair point.

46:47.554 --> 46:48.597
Hmm.

46:48.597 --> 46:51.391
I know how important
those files were to you, boss.

46:51.391 --> 46:52.809
We didn't want to let you down.

46:54.603 --> 46:55.729
Gentlemen.

47:16.375 --> 47:22.798
Fuck! Fuck, fuck, fuck!

47:24.508 --> 47:27.010
God!

47:27.010 --> 47:30.931
I'm back.

47:30.931 --> 47:33.267
- We bungled the whole thing.
- Howard?

47:33.267 --> 47:34.851
It was a disaster.

47:35.852 --> 47:38.063
This was my last chance,
it's-- it's over.

47:38.063 --> 47:41.275
Yes. I'm-- I'm sorry to hear
that but--

47:41.275 --> 47:42.901
Dot, I know you
don't like Gordon,

47:42.901 --> 47:45.737
but we blew it.
It is over! It...

47:45.737 --> 47:47.072
Maybe it's fate trying to--

47:47.072 --> 47:49.032
Lisa is dropping out of college.

47:49.032 --> 47:51.118
Christ,
I did not drop out!

47:52.035 --> 47:53.036
Lisa?

47:54.329 --> 47:55.831
Surprise.

47:55.831 --> 47:57.249
What are you doing home?

47:57.249 --> 47:58.584
I don't know,
I just decided

47:58.584 --> 48:01.128
it wasn't a great way
to spend my limited time

48:01.128 --> 48:03.213
on this planet,
listening to a bunch

48:03.213 --> 48:05.090
of establishment tools.

48:05.090 --> 48:07.175
Well, sounds like dropping
out to me.

48:07.175 --> 48:09.136
See! I knew he was going
to say that.

48:09.136 --> 48:12.139
- Honey. She's very upset.
- Yeah, well, so am I!

48:12.139 --> 48:16.101
Does this mean that I can
s-- skip college, too?

48:16.101 --> 48:17.185
No.
No!

48:17.185 --> 48:20.564
Shut up!
- We both had very bad days.

48:20.564 --> 48:24.776
Papa tried to deliver
a very big project

48:24.776 --> 48:27.904
for President Nixon,
which did not go well,

48:27.904 --> 48:32.117
and you had whatever
difficulties you had.

48:32.117 --> 48:34.286
Take tonight. Get some sleep.

48:34.286 --> 48:36.622
In the morning,
I'll drive you back, pumpkin.

48:36.622 --> 48:38.373
No! First of all,
to hell with Nixon!

48:38.373 --> 48:39.541
And I'm not going back there

48:39.541 --> 48:41.335
- you can't make me go back!
- Keep your voice down.

48:41.335 --> 48:44.046
Why! Can Nixon hear me?

48:46.506 --> 48:47.924
Try the breathing, sweetie.

48:49.051 --> 48:50.510
Okay.

48:50.510 --> 48:53.180
You've got this under control.
You don't need me.

48:57.934 --> 48:59.186
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

48:59.186 --> 49:03.690
You can thank your lucky stars
the LAPD blamed it on a junkie.

49:03.690 --> 49:06.026
Goddamn amateur night
with those Cubans.

49:06.026 --> 49:08.070
And I am going to tell
that to-- to Krogh.

49:08.070 --> 49:11.323
Those Cubans improvised
that whole junkie ruse!

49:11.323 --> 49:15.118
- They saved our asses!
- Oh, hey, Doug.

49:15.118 --> 49:17.162
Would you say this "black op"
is indicative

49:17.162 --> 49:19.539
of the professionalism
and general competence

49:19.539 --> 49:21.124
of your CIA?

49:21.124 --> 49:23.960
Those men were betrayed
by this country

49:23.960 --> 49:27.214
and yet, here they are,
putting their asses on the line

49:27.214 --> 49:29.800
for it again and for zero pay!

49:29.800 --> 49:32.594
Do you know anyone
from the FBI

49:32.594 --> 49:35.597
doing this
kind of high-risk work for free?

49:36.264 --> 49:37.432
Damn right you don't.

49:37.432 --> 49:40.435
That's loyalty!
That's patriotism!

49:43.146 --> 49:47.359
Do not lecture me
on patriotism, friend.

49:48.902 --> 49:50.779
You can go right in.
- Thank you.

49:50.779 --> 49:54.157
And let the record show,
Gordon Liddy shits red,

49:54.157 --> 49:55.784
white, and blue.
Hiya, fellas.

49:55.784 --> 49:57.869
John! Uh...

49:59.287 --> 50:01.748
...uh, Gordon,
uh, this is, John Dean.

50:01.748 --> 50:02.874
Have a seat.

50:15.345 --> 50:19.599
S-- so, uh, waiting for Bud?

50:19.599 --> 50:22.310
Oh, no. Bu--
No. No, Bud's out.

50:25.272 --> 50:26.565
Gentlemen, you're fired.

50:30.485 --> 50:31.987
Congratulations, you're hired.

50:31.987 --> 50:34.030
Liddy, you now work
for the Committee

50:34.030 --> 50:35.574
to re-elect the President.

50:35.574 --> 50:40.120
The President needs men
of action and your new mission

50:40.120 --> 50:43.832
is to make sure he wins
this election.

50:43.832 --> 50:45.500
Liddy, we'd like you
to be the Committee's

50:45.500 --> 50:46.752
new chief counsel.

50:48.462 --> 50:49.463
Oh.

50:50.797 --> 50:51.923
Thank you, John.

50:52.758 --> 50:53.800
I'm honored.

50:55.802 --> 50:59.514
I hope Howard will be available
to advise.

51:02.809 --> 51:04.811
I will indeed.

51:04.811 --> 51:07.606
Very nice.
You'll report to Jeb Magruder.

51:07.606 --> 51:10.400
He's deputy head over there
and keep me briefed.

51:11.735 --> 51:13.612
S... so, I'm clear, Bud--

51:13.612 --> 51:16.198
The President doesn't think
he has the stomach

51:16.198 --> 51:17.783
for bare-knuckle tactics.

51:17.783 --> 51:19.618
Too much little old lady
in him.

51:19.618 --> 51:21.286
Yeah.

51:21.286 --> 51:23.121
But your commitment,
your zeal--

51:23.121 --> 51:25.499
Let's just say, you
impressed the right people.

51:27.375 --> 51:32.130
So, uh, what are we talking
about here?

51:32.130 --> 51:37.803
Espionage, sabotage, uh,
infiltration, disinformation,

51:37.803 --> 51:39.554
electronic surveillance,
re-- recruiting

51:39.554 --> 51:43.058
and planting moles, your various
and sundry dirty tricks.

51:43.058 --> 51:45.393
Same shit they do
to us every election.

51:45.393 --> 51:48.939
Work up a proposal
and budget and, uh,

51:48.939 --> 51:52.442
dazzle us.
Uh, say, John,

51:53.151 --> 51:55.111
when you say budget...

51:56.780 --> 51:59.241
what size ballpark
are we playing in here?

52:00.408 --> 52:01.827
How much do you think
you'll need?

52:01.827 --> 52:02.869
Oh. I'd...

52:03.411 --> 52:04.871
Hmm.

52:04.871 --> 52:11.294
For the, uh, scope and, uh,
scale of what it is you're

52:12.170 --> 52:14.631
envisioning, um, I'd say...

52:16.132 --> 52:18.552
a million dollars?

52:20.595 --> 52:24.516
Sure. Whatever you guys need.

52:24.516 --> 52:26.768
♪ ("THE BEST IS YET TO COME"
BY FRANK SINATRA PLAYING) ♪

52:26.768 --> 52:28.895
Sure.

52:28.895 --> 52:34.067
<i>♪ Out of the tree of life
I just picked me a plum ♪</i>

52:37.821 --> 52:39.322
<i>♪ You came along ♪</i>

52:39.322 --> 52:42.742
<i>♪ And everything's
Startin' to hum ♪</i>

52:45.996 --> 52:47.873
- What've we got?
<i>- ♪ Still it's a... ♪</i>

52:47.873 --> 52:49.457
One of our cameras
was used in an op

52:49.457 --> 52:51.960
for the White House.
They forgot to take the film out

52:51.960 --> 52:53.962
of the camera
when they gave it back.

52:54.963 --> 52:56.214
What the fuck is this?

52:56.214 --> 53:00.468
<i>♪ The best is yet to come
And, babe, won't that be fine? ♪</i>

53:03.972 --> 53:06.600
<i>♪ You think you've seen
The sun ♪</i>

53:06.600 --> 53:09.853
<i>♪ But you ain't seen it shine ♪</i>

53:12.731 --> 53:17.110
<i>♪ A-wait till the warm-up's
Underway ♪</i>

53:17.110 --> 53:20.113
<i>♪ Wait till our lips have met ♪</i>

53:21.531 --> 53:26.077
<i>♪ And wait till you see
That sunshine day ♪</i>

53:26.077 --> 53:28.914
